<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870306-0038 </DOCNO><HL> General RefractoriesTo Sell Europe UnitsTo an Austrian Group</HL><DD> 03/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GRXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> BALA CYNWYD, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Refractories Co. said it agreed to sell its European group operations to an Austrian investor group headed by Girozentrale Bank of Austria for about $62 million. The group includes refractory and building products operations.    The maker of refractory materials for industrial furnaces said the businesses being sold include refractories manufacturing plants in Austria and West Germany; building product plants in Austria, West Germany and Greece; magnesite mining operations in Austria and Greece and related sales companies in several countries.    The European group had sales of $186 million in 1985. Total sales for the company that year were $316 million. Sales figures for 1986 weren't available.    Raymond G. Perelman, chairman and chief executive officer, said the transaction is part of the company's previously announced efforts to restructure.    The transaction is subject to approval by General Refractories shareholders. </TEXT></DOC>